- “DINER” – uses D and I, both still allowed, and satisfies all constraints.

DINER:
- Uses D, I, N, E, R – none of the banned letters.
- Positions: E is in slot 3 (allowed), R is in slot 5 (allowed).  
- Provides new letters D, I, N to test.

So DINER is a solid third guess.
